<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="302" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,261,863]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,802,828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is the Latin noun “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kang and Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[785,867,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Takagioma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladius">
<emphasis box="[785,867,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="302">gladius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (sword), which refers to the sword-like aedeagal shaft in ventral view.
</paragraph>
